codex
Implemented the Node.js/Express room reservation app in the workspace.

Created:
- `package.json` with Express, EJS, sessions, SQLite, bcrypt, Helmet
- `server.js`
- `src/db.js`
- EJS views under `views/`
- CSS under `public/styles.css`
- `README.md` with local run instructions for port `5059`

Core behavior included:
- Register/login/logout
- Daily room availability grid
- Booking by room/date/time slot
- Database-level unique constraint preventing double-booking
- Users can view and cancel only their own bookings
- SQLite database auto-created and seeded on first start

Per the workspace instructions, I only wrote files and did not install dependencies or run the app.
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..85fa93de82daf2a5e48ad45c20aeeefd1eddac23
--- /dev/null
+++ b/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,14 @@
+# Room Reservation System
+
+A Node.js/Express app for booking rooms by day and time slot. It uses SQLite for users, rooms, time slots, bookings, and session storage. A unique database constraint prevents double-booking the same room, date, and slot.
+
+## Run locally
+
+```bash
+npm install
+npm start
+```
+
+Open `http://localhost:5059`.
+
+The app creates `data/reservations.sqlite` automatically on first start, then seeds a few rooms and time slots.
